Former West Ham defender Jordan Spence has joined MK Dons on a one-year-deal following his release this summer.

The 24-year-old spent last season on loan with the League 1 club and made 31 appearances for Karl Robinson's side.

Spence left Upton Park on a free transfer having joined the Hammers as a youth back in 2004.

